# @envirobyte/ui Component Library Standards

## Component Rules

- Every new component needs a Storybook story in the same directory.
- Components must be generic — no app-specific logic, no API calls, no state management.
- Export every public component and its prop types from `src/index.ts`.
- Tailwind classes only; no inline styles.

## Project Structure

- Components live in `src/components/generic/` (complex) or `src/components/primitives/` (base elements).
- Shared utilities in `src/lib/`.
- Theme/provider wrapper in `src/provider/`.
- Global styles in `src/styles.css`.

## Build

- Built with `tsup` + PostCSS. Run `npm run build` to produce `dist/`.
- Published to GitHub Packages as `@envirobyte/ui`.
- Consumers (`datapivot-fe`, `rim-fe`) use `LOCAL_UI=1` for local dev.

## Consumers

- `datapivot-fe` and `rim-fe` depend on this package.
- `emissionx-frontend` does NOT use this package — it has its own component set.
- Breaking changes to exported components or props will affect both consumer apps.
